<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\19_wizard_dungeon\19_cv_orrery_controls</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>23</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>The orrery controls are oiled and ready to be manipulated. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Enter the coordinates for the Huntress legend constellations.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>As the last number settles into place, you hear the sound of dormant gears beginning to turn. A low vibration builds under your feet.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Read the plaque.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>&lt;i&gt;Bekarna,

If you're reading this, you've forgotten again. You blasted your mind to bits trying to scribe Bekarna's Clarity of Thought. I'm sorry.&lt;/i&gt;</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Manipulate the controls.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>You pull on levers and enter random numbers into the coordinates. When nothing happens, gears spin in the machine and reset the numbers to zero. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Examine the controls more closely.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>The levers adjust a series of numbered dials which correspond to the altitude and azimuth of celestial bodies.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>You enter the coordinates you've collected so far. Nothing happens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>The control mechanism of this orrery is tarnished, though recently oiled. Some of the levers show signs of meddling.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>A plaque to the side bears the mark of a hand swiping to brush away dust.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>The orrery has rotated into the correct position already.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>&lt;i&gt;Never doubt yourself. Your years of research were well-spent even if no one called you 'archmage' at the end of them. Even if they laughed.

I know you remember the legend of your favorite Huana constellation, the Huntress.&lt;/i&gt;</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>&lt;i&gt;When you need a little confidence, set the coordinates of the Huntress and the three stages of her tale into this orrery. 

You can do more with half a brain than most competent wizards. So get back to work.&lt;/i&gt;</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If I don't survive our adventures, promise me you'll burn all my books." He's blushing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>Whatever the mechanism is meant to do, it will only work with the right set of coordinates.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>Three more coordinates are still required.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Two of the coordinates are missing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>One final set of coordinates is required.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>&lt;i&gt;Love, 
Bekarna&lt;/i&gt;</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Four sets of coordinates can be entered at once, which will spin the inner mechanism of the globe in a precise combination of turns. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>